  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" GBJ Hotels Private Limited versus Sriharan Sripathmanathan & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_4_2444_2450','2025INSC585'); ><font size='4'> <strong>GBJ HOTELS PRIVATE LIMITED<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>SRIHARAN SRIPATHMANATHAN & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2444</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 585</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007022025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : DIPANKAR DATTA, MANMOHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration During the proceedings before the High Court, the Court accepted a better price for the creditor. The offer of the GRT Hotels was accepted by Edelweiss ARCL and it was agreed that the amount deposited of GBJ Hotels would be returned. Aggrieved, GBJ Hotels filed on the ground that sanctity of the auction under the SARFAESI Act has been breached in the process. Headnotes&dagger; Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 &ndash; Debt Recovery &ndash; Auction &ndash; Respondents no.1 and 2<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 28-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) No. 7301/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_4_2444_2450','2025INSC585','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitvi